The Los Angeles Dodgers acquired
catcher Ramon Hernandez from the Colorado Rockies for pitcher
Aaron Harang, the Major League Baseball team said in a
statement.  Hernandez, 36, batted .217 with five home runs and 28 runs
batted in over 52 games for Colorado last season. He has a .264
average, 166 homers and 751 RBI over 14 major-league seasons
with four teams.  Harang, a 34-year-old right-hander, was 10-10 with a 3.61
earned run average in 31 starts with the Dodgers in 2012. Heâ€™s
